10e37bc1-748c-4d31-b720-df2d8ffccc50.do_description: To make the output, you have to...move all of the single blocks to the inside of the orange square
10e37bc1-748c-4d31-b720-df2d8ffccc50.grid_description: The output grid size...the output remains the same.
10e37bc1-748c-4d31-b720-df2d8ffccc50.see_description: In the input, you should see...an factor of outside flipped inside.

1f88ed35-4b0b-4c44-b0c9-2dd04f12ecf8.do_description: To make the output, you have to...  copy the input grid to the output workspace.  Move each of the interior corner colored pixels to the exterior corner opposite of their input position.  Meaning, move the upper left interior pixel such that its corner is touching the lower left corner of the lower left corner pixel of the monochromatic rectangle or square.  You're moving pixel at a 45 degree angle to the exterior opposite corner, do that with each interior corner square to create the correct output grid.
1f88ed35-4b0b-4c44-b0c9-2dd04f12ecf8.grid_description: The output grid size... is the same as the input.
1f88ed35-4b0b-4c44-b0c9-2dd04f12ecf8.see_description: In the input, you should see...a grid with a square or rectangle composed of monochromatic pixels with a colored pixel at each of the interior corners of the rectangle.

562920cf-fdb2-41be-a4a3-34d1a8a987f4.do_description: To make the output, you have to...Black background with blue border black fill. colors swapped to opposite corner of blue square
562920cf-fdb2-41be-a4a3-34d1a8a987f4.grid_description: The output grid size...Grid size leaving the same
562920cf-fdb2-41be-a4a3-34d1a8a987f4.see_description: In the input, you should see...Black background with blue border. Red square top left in blue square. Gray fill in right top corner. Purple fill in bottom left corner and green fill in bottom right corner.

a36e9d65-01e1-4b13-b42f-3c5f064ad586.do_description: To make the output, you have to...take the different colored squares from the inside corners of the square and move them to the opposite outside corner of the square. For example if there is a green square on the inside bottom left corner, move it to the outside top right corner. The rest of the squares will be black.
a36e9d65-01e1-4b13-b42f-3c5f064ad586.grid_description: The output grid size... is the same as the input.
a36e9d65-01e1-4b13-b42f-3c5f064ad586.see_description: In the input, you should see...a grid with a square in one color. There will be four small different colored squares on the inside corners of the square. The rest of the inside of the square and the rest of the grid is black.
